					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-528535#post-1511437</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-528535/out-of-time#post-1511437</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 18 Jul 2012 17:35:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ChazzK</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1203158</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The whole &quot;Stop all time in the rest of the universe&quot; and &quot;step out of time/speed my time up immeasurably&quot; is kind of a moot point to the observer, in whose perspective this story is written.</p> <p>The REAL problem comes with the fact that, logically, if you were to &quot;stop time&quot; on a single object, within a very small fraction of a second it would be *very* far away.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
